<body>
    <h1>Embeddable KYC and Risk Review UI</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h2 local-id=3D"22da74eb53c8" id=3D"EmbeddableKYCandRiskReviewUI-Ba=
ckground">Background</h2>
<p local-id=3D"49f36f9cb0c2">This Epic encapsulates the requirements of an =
embeddable UI component. Its main purpose is to collect information from en=
d users and route it to the KYC and Risk Review Microservice to perform rel=
evant checks. It will have configurable branding and document collection fl=
ows to serve the application client.</p>
<p local-id=3D"e0355034380b">The first client of this embeddable UI compone=
nt will be Verivend. Verivend is a capital raising and investor portal plat=
form serving both General Partners (GPs) and Limited Partners (LPs). Histor=
ically, Verivend has operated in a model where GPs handle the KYC of their =
own investors, allowing rapid LP onboarding without a verification gate. Ho=
wever, certain sensitive platform capabilities =E2=80=94 such as registerin=
g multiple bank accounts against an LP organization =E2=80=94 now require V=
erivend to perform direct LP KYC. A parallel need exists on the GP side: Ve=
rivend has always verified GPs and sponsors manually through an admin-drive=
n process, and automating that workflow is a strategic priority.</p>
<p local-id=3D"60d4b8982b19">Verivend will use the embeddable component to =
collect information required to perform KYC on both LPs and GPs across thre=
e verification paths: Individual (solo), Individual (joint account), and En=
tity. The component owns the collection experience end-to-end; Verivend own=
s the surrounding workflow, path selection, and verification lifecycle. Res=
ults of checks will surface in the Verivend UI natively =E2=80=94 the embed=
dable component collects and submits; it does not display verification outc=
omes.</p>
<p local-id=3D"a83e6d5f8311">A key architectural driver is that additional =
persons required for multi-person verification flows (joint account co-hold=
ers, entity beneficial owners) are likely not Verivend platform users and m=
ay never be. Their identity verification must occur outside the Verivend au=
thenticated portal via a token-authenticated standalone link served by Inte=
rro. This two-surface model =E2=80=94 embedded component for the primary us=
er, standalone link for additional persons =E2=80=94 is a core design const=
raint for the MVP.</p>
<p local-id=3D"f89d823085dc">The MVP will support configurable branding, a =
set of default user flows for individuals and entities, country-aware field=
 collection, and server-side session persistence. Future iterations will ad=
d configurability of collected fields and documents.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"37e83e67-d135-4443-83f0-a9c5e81e5418">
<h2 local-id=3D"14e42e5ac037" id=3D"EmbeddableKYCandRiskReviewUI-MVPRequire=
ments">MVP Requirements</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"8d9fd1a960c4" id=3D"EmbeddableKYCandRiskReviewUI-Configurab=
leBranding">Configurable Branding</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"22a203ef-4038-4c43-88ea-cfef78508d50">
<li local-id=3D"151048ec-5176-4ef5-a261-82c8039125b8">
<p local-id=3D"b43f7ab6bec3">Ability to configure primary, accent, heading,=
 and text colors depending on the application client</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"449bd5dd-b97e-47d8-b5e5-6df0afa3a7a0">
<p local-id=3D"b3ed1a524a60">Ability to configure the font depending on the=
 application client</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"587c8cad-9db8-4d97-a72b-91b8829e3902">
<p local-id=3D"ef469f556af0">Ability to configure a client logo or wordmark=
; "Powered by Interro" lockup is always present and must meet a defined min=
imum size and placement spec</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e21c6599-717b-4742-b983-e122c5d3cd90">
<p local-id=3D"28980c7b73b7">Client-supplied color configurations must be v=
alidated against minimum WCAG 2.1 AA contrast ratios at configuration time,=
 with a warning surfaced for non-compliant values</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"994e4c50-e059-46d7-a30b-517a7a34ba64">
<p local-id=3D"8850fa022439"><strong>Product Question (Marco):</strong> Are=
 we required to disclose the use of Alloy in the Alloy MSA to end users wit=
hin the component UI? Resolve and capture as a hard requirement or explicit=
 deferral with owner.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"dc0f86c9abc3" id=3D"EmbeddableKYCandRiskReviewUI-Verificati=
onPaths">Verification Paths</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"05c9c49b-e393-4b36-b8e8-3f5a2d2fd63d">
<li local-id=3D"a290bbb1-48e1-4c58-968f-92a36cae94d3">
<p local-id=3D"127247b5bea4">Component must support three first-class verif=
ication paths:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"0196bcf6-da89-4939-a11e-72ad195ae702">
<li local-id=3D"73dfc190-d4f3-452e-bac3-5640f925f375">
<p local-id=3D"7d7aac6701b4"><strong>Individual (Solo):</strong> Single nat=
ural person; 4 steps; 1 person KYC'd</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"de6e4f68-b00f-4011-8dca-0ac432dfbbeb">
<p local-id=3D"c5aab681f729"><strong>Individual (Joint Account):</strong> 2=
=E2=80=935 co-equal natural persons; 5 steps; each holder independently KYC=
'd</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"515abf04-fd21-4d53-9b69-785ba2acd01f">
<p local-id=3D"e41acae7f384"><strong>Entity:</strong> LLC, Corporation, Tru=
st, Partnership, etc.; 5 steps; 1 authorized representative + N beneficial =
owners (=E2=89=A525% ownership) KYC'd</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"1e6b3298-9f91-4442-b63a-b1ccec2d9ec4">
<p local-id=3D"81b6eeae195b">Joint account verification must be a native fl=
ow =E2=80=94 not a workaround on top of entity KYB logic. Co-equal natural =
persons with no underlying entity is not a standard provider pattern and mu=
st be designed for explicitly.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"107b30f7-d79b-47b0-b428-b74e649b7c7b">
<p local-id=3D"6d14ead3f6d1">Path type is passed as a session initializatio=
n parameter by the host application, bypassing the component's built-in pat=
h selector. The component's built-in selector must remain functional for co=
ntexts where the host defers path selection to the component.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"734063b667f8" id=3D"EmbeddableKYCandRiskReviewUI-Multi-Pers=
onOrchestration">Multi-Person Orchestration</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"075fc9e3-f85c-46f2-ae60-5669a0b31892">
<li local-id=3D"e27e0a1d-9c80-4e27-916e-7b42f35e84d9">
<p local-id=3D"d7ea127c3591">Two-phase model for all non-solo paths:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"f49156de-330f-44f7-80f5-034c6be98e37">
<li local-id=3D"50662950-c1ec-41f1-b6eb-b3bac3d58848">
<p local-id=3D"3f2cc238ec15"><strong>Phase 1 (Primary user):</strong> The V=
erivend account holder enters biographical data for all additional persons =
(name, DOB, nationality, ownership % where applicable) within the embedded =
component session</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"92d54c0d-fda4-4b37-81ad-77208dc3375c">
<p local-id=3D"0231818afd0d"><strong>Phase 2 (Additional persons):</strong>=
 Each additional person receives a token-authenticated verification link vi=
a email and SMS, served by Interro outside the Verivend portal, requiring n=
o Verivend account. The Primary user will be able to enter the details of a=
dditional persons as well if they have the information. If the additional p=
ersons are still required to do an ID upload + selfie via mobile workflow, =
they will be able to see and confirm the information that was entered on th=
eir behalf.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"6f34e6a3-af1a-481f-90dd-9b29069dc6a0">
<p local-id=3D"7ff23a0f2fbc">Primary user sees real-time aggregate progress=
 within the component (e.g., "2 of 4 holders verified") and understands thi=
s is a multi-party process that will not complete instantly</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"442e09ce-8045-46f0-947c-b96d76e2c112">
<p local-id=3D"121b2365cc03">Interro must support reminder/re-send of verif=
ication links for persons who have not completed</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e1b5b16c-8af0-473f-b133-eb53e2f0cdb9">
<p local-id=3D"3fa73878cca6">Standalone verification links must be branded =
consistently with the host client's active theme configuration</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f16f6e75-9739-4f7a-b201-a12ad9309a4a">
<p local-id=3D"34b38b967fcb">Standalone link expiry policy must be defined;=
 behavior on expiry must be specified (e.g., re-send flow, graceful error s=
creen)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4e730f69-dd3c-4ecf-b256-c1710030bca0">
<p local-id=3D"b588275ac13d"><strong>Open Question:</strong> Can the primar=
y user complete identity verification on behalf of an additional person (e.=
g., a co-located spouse)? The answer determines whether liveness/selfie che=
cks are required and whether self-verification is mandatory per person. Thi=
s must be resolved before detailed flow design for joint accounts is finali=
zed.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"450107da7e3b" id=3D"EmbeddableKYCandRiskReviewUI-SessionIni=
tializationContract">Session Initialization Contract</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"a7fa8bc0-4753-4151-aa87-75732af8a1b2">
<li local-id=3D"14b45f38-196a-447d-8716-520eec715d4f">
<p local-id=3D"8e8acad2a8aa">Verivend passes the following parameters at se=
ssion creation:</p></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"99=
c7b652-189e-42f8-9922-e8d5c3c8f8ce" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"2e39fe3b-46fe-47b9-ba94-45f0c477e659">
<th data-local-id=3D"ae6f232b-a1a8-4c44-8315-d48f5072123f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"bdb923ef4cb2">Parameter</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"58fa58f9-83bc-4731-8d8e-7dc315064c9c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"eb9a6597eda3">Type</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"b2bc55df-e3ab-48f5-a4c3-a88bcf789762" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"312dee24f6e5">When Passed</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"7e75e50e-32cb-4bee-a0e2-9b36454ee576">
<td data-local-id=3D"573c70b8-58e1-439f-9a9b-a507c8a1d8de" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7c2603b81f89">Path type</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"6b3192a0-57b6-4b96-b119-bddb3a25a8ea" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"85d92ec2c688"><code>individual</code> / <code>joint</code> /=
 <code>entity</code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"c86d3342-a8c4-40b9-9635-dfe6365365bb" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"976ea5ff8333">Always</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"0b620ba8-316f-4428-a752-94309af625ff">
