<ul local-id=3D"9105d399-d535-46f6-b25e-cfdffa7a98a8">
<li local-id=3D"2ca44fd9-c4b6-4d4a-ac5d-ad5db07ac79e">
<p local-id=3D"f2ee96919dc4">Bulk export of all person data and all documen=
ts per session must be achievable in a single or minimal number of API call=
s</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8f3f94a4-9650-4ffc-a6b7-4116b26cc7c2">
<p local-id=3D"1ef33a0c4624">Retrieval access must remain available for a m=
inimum of 10 years; Interro must provide advance notice before any data pur=
ge</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"1677eb529ac0" id=3D"EmbeddableKYCandRiskReviewUI-Returned-f=
or-CorrectionsFlow">Returned-for-Corrections Flow</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"a4610ba9-bba4-472c-8319-e950728e0fd9">
<li local-id=3D"4920f87c-c583-421b-beb5-f51da688bec4">
<p local-id=3D"49e4b1c3a669">The component must support a <strong>correctio=
n/re-entry mode</strong> in which a previously submitted session is re-open=
ed for editing and resubmission</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5e8a5f56-e705-4ee5-b860-e4b47ccb889e">
<p local-id=3D"e50a31531284">Entity formation document uploads must pass a =
<strong>programmatic image quality gate</strong> before the user can advanc=
e =E2=80=94 this eliminates unreadable document submissions before they rea=
ch a reviewer <em>(see Technical Requirements)</em></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3121a7b5-b844-4005-9b54-68cdcc77a533">
<p local-id=3D"13b4415e4ec8">Two rejection modes must be supported:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"c3163451-1729-4949-aeef-5ee88dee88f9">
<li local-id=3D"3e540f53-6f1b-4ede-8ebe-46b289caee1c">
<p local-id=3D"101ce4906204"><strong>Retry:</strong> Session is returned fo=
r correction; user corrects and resubmits</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"bbb10002-5b86-484c-920b-17b793714ec5">
<p local-id=3D"eb6727afcabe"><strong>Final:</strong> Submission rejected; u=
ser directed to contact support</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"b0114006-51e6-451e-9a48-020e6c8ac445">
<p local-id=3D"2995eaa627f3">Re-completed correction flows must emit <code>=
flow:submitted</code> identically to an original submission</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7529bf01-adce-4920-9946-1e53cd78ec30">
<p local-id=3D"29b7b9451993"><strong>The design of the correction re-entry =
experience (reviewer-annotated form vs. full session reset) is an open ques=
tion =E2=80=94 see Correction Flow Design Question at the bottom of this do=
cument</strong></p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"2c32bb85fb4e" id=3D"EmbeddableKYCandRiskReviewUI-TechnicalR=
equirements">Technical Requirements</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"5788365d-acf7-4daa-b70d-395a666c0157">
<li local-id=3D"a08a0864-ca3c-4f3b-8837-bd9450c82f3e">
<p local-id=3D"75361417b782">Served in an iframe; iframe subdomain format: =
<code>{client}.interro.com</code> per application client</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e615bd24-420e-4e34-8c50-cce8905ff02a">
<p local-id=3D"83892b4d5111"><strong>Open Question:</strong> iframe vs. Jav=
aScript SDK =E2=80=94 tradeoffs for theming, event communication, CSP, and =
security isolation must be formally evaluated and a decision documented bef=
ore implementation begins</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"30032d07-4ede-46c5-aeaf-34a7d8a4a75d">
<p local-id=3D"b7cc8f8e7ece">Able to serve both desktop and mobile browser =
sessions; mobile responsiveness is a first-class requirement, not a nice-to=
-have</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d6288215-d300-4af6-a2c2-2bd065e1d778">
<p local-id=3D"3ed1c8b31819">QR code handoff to mobile for document capture=
 (user on desktop can scan to complete document upload on mobile)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6882a842-47b4-4930-99ae-3a21febc42ce">
<p local-id=3D"21b1d8bc0c62">Input masking for sensitive fields (SSN, passp=
ort number, etc.)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4c8d9541-13a9-43ca-8e7a-b42dad41dbe4">
<p local-id=3D"7ceb8948c85a">Document upload with preview and crop</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a0438ecf038b">
<p local-id=3D"b8f2d7c45440">Entity formation document uploads must pass a =
programmatic image quality gate before the user can advance. The component =
must reject uploads that fall below a minimum legibility threshold =E2=80=
=94 insufficient resolution, excessive blur, or poor contrast =E2=80=94 and=
 prompt the user to re-capture or re-scan before proceeding. This gate appl=
ies to entity formation documents only; identity document capture quality i=
s enforced by the Socure SDK and is not in scope here.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"08a36d73-1780-4402-a6bf-e96af69b82ef">
<p local-id=3D"26abae03c21f">Inline field validation: unable to advance if =
regex validation is not met; error message with correct format instructions=
 rendered in contrast-compliant color beneath the field</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"149c14fc-79a5-4297-ac6a-44962a813c25">
<p local-id=3D"2ec2748e3d7e">Error messages must serve distinct, human-read=
able copy for each failure mode: field validation, document upload failure =
(size exceeded, unsupported format, upload interrupted), network failure, m=
icroservice timeout</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3d6b39ba-2fed-46c9-a1b2-1a55b3ccae7b">
<p local-id=3D"3d41e08925c9">Network failure and microservice timeout must =
have a graceful degradation path with retry capability =E2=80=94 the user m=
ust never lose data silently</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"70d44dcd-d3db-47a1-92ec-d79d525b0161">
<p local-id=3D"f6a9fedbf9a2">Content Security Policy headers must govern if=
rame-permitted resource loading</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"aaa2ead7-ab67-4001-a85b-603929dde89a">
<p local-id=3D"0bad85e632a2">WCAG 2.1 AA conformance: keyboard navigation, =
screen reader support, programmatic association of error messages with fiel=
ds (<code>aria-describedby</code>), focus management between steps</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d149cfbc-fcbd-4434-91c9-e77cca5e504d">
<p local-id=3D"73b5a13f8b2a"><strong>Open Question:</strong> iframe resize =
behavior must be defined =E2=80=94 fixed height, auto-resize via postMessag=
e, or scrollable container</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"7a4cd370f5f8" id=3D"EmbeddableKYCandRiskReviewUI-Session&am=
p;StateManagement">Session &amp; State Management</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"3a07f08a-00f9-499b-8981-4b3e0b03159c">
<li local-id=3D"af32c3e4-fdc6-4c9e-8612-5e6f8d603346">
<p local-id=3D"feacc01c39e6">Server-side auto-save on every step completion=
 =E2=80=94 not browser session storage, not localStorage</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5b1d7ea1-c3e7-4d62-884c-4cbe6310476d">
<p local-id=3D"77e06673e695">All previously completed steps and uploaded do=
cuments survive browser close, logout, navigation away, and full login/logo=
ut cycles</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ccb0ad20-032e-4d0a-b827-9bd46b289e2b">
<p local-id=3D"5ddce4b272db">Cross-device resume: user can start on desktop=
 and finish on mobile; component loads at first incomplete step with all pr=
ior data intact</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6d43f4c5-c47e-4636-bc56-1f1a398c15c8">
<p local-id=3D"ccc68953942d">Sessions must remain resumable for weeks</p></=
li>
<li local-id=3D"368cfcef-be56-461b-86a5-52cb1db60d8a">
<p local-id=3D"1ecd8ab8b4ca">Session token expiry policy must be defined; t=
he user-facing experience when a token is invalidated or expires mid-flow m=
ust be specified</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"688b207d-032d-4f76-ada2-aa255600260d">
<p local-id=3D"f7b1f3b76d1e">Concurrent session behavior must be defined: w=
hat occurs if the same user opens the flow on two devices simultaneously</p=
></li>
<li local-id=3D"ed8431ce-a147-423e-9b4d-45bce8c23f21">
<p local-id=3D"b97aee0b57f4">Component must reflect session progress before=
 the user interacts =E2=80=94 host application can query session status via=
 API to show "Verification in progress =E2=80=94 60% complete" without load=
ing the component</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"abdbd70aedbe" id=3D"EmbeddableKYCandRiskReviewUI-DataRetent=
ion&amp;PIIHandling">Data Retention &amp; PII Handling</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"18e7def9-c407-476d-a29b-d3396bc74a97">
<li local-id=3D"19d69b4a-d245-4a5b-8c7a-215d762a124f">
<p local-id=3D"796c1ee01ada">Document uploads are routed directly from the =
component to Interro infrastructure =E2=80=94 never through the host applic=
ation's frontend</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0835a873-1e67-4cea-97b3-f2876c4b7f2e">
<p local-id=3D"fdd4a8b7f41d">PII in transit: TLS 1.2+ required for all comp=
onent, Interro backend, and Verivend backend communication</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c1f48400-3b73-43c9-b4ac-544c692fbe73">
<p local-id=3D"28e3504e3662">PII at rest: SSNs, passport numbers, and ident=
ity documents encrypted at rest in Interro's storage</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e8c05ea8-68bc-45e2-9f9a-b48460e0e88a">
<p local-id=3D"6ccff5249286">Verivend retains a full copy of all data: pers=
onal information, document images, and screening results =E2=80=94 retrieve=
d via API after flow completion and stored in Verivend's domain model under=
 its own encryption pipeline</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a1187038-51d1-4182-8925-81e7b89130e6">
<p local-id=3D"2e1f0a8b8ad3">Document upload constraints: max 10MB per file=
; accepted formats: PDF, JPEG, PNG</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"344efa5161be" id=3D"EmbeddableKYCandRiskReviewUI-Extensibil=
ityRequirements">Extensibility Requirements</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"a7a938ab-f250-4e8b-86ca-3fd4202aeb4a">
<li local-id=3D"65b2b3fd-659e-4d85-9057-3ecb58a17fc5">
<p local-id=3D"b026de389f83">User can select their country and expect corre=
ctly labeled fields for their jurisdiction (e.g., address fields, identity =
document types)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0c15fed4-05af-478d-b206-507ae989fd6e">
<p local-id=3D"f45280ee2950"><strong>Non-MVP:</strong> Jurisdictional requi=
rements around data processing disclosures (GDPR/CCPA consent steps pre-col=
lection) must be scoped and either added to a future iteration or explicitl=
y deferred with rationale and owner</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"3f3fc191e788" id=3D"EmbeddableKYCandRiskReviewUI-Throughput=
&amp;PerformanceRequirements">Throughput &amp; Performance Requirements</h3=
>
<p local-id=3D"fb37febaa479">Verivend's expected verification volume is few=
er than <strong>1,000 sessions per month</strong>. That being said, we don=
=E2=80=99t want to size a bridge based on how many people swim across the r=
iver (Words of wisdom from Balaji). The component and its backend services =
must be capable of handling at least <strong>200 concurrent sessions</stron=
g> to accommodate peak usage and future client growth without re-architecti=
ng.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"0dbfccfc-45e6-447c-a92b-1a61bf6ea86a">
<li local-id=3D"65ad14c7-293b-421f-83bb-7d269f1e3045">
<p local-id=3D"472392c34ac7"><strong>Component load time:</strong> Initial =
render must complete within 3 seconds on a standard broadband connection</p=
></li>
<li local-id=3D"db6a4bbc-f3f0-48d7-bba0-3da60da03735">
<p local-id=3D"17e8357990f7"><strong>Step save latency:</strong> Server-sid=
e auto-save must respond within 2 seconds; the user must not be blocked fro=
m advancing while a save is in progress</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"20248ac9-7f83-4ba2-89cc-61011c1fb6aa">
<p local-id=3D"32d8bf3752fd"><strong>Document upload:</strong> Upload of a =
max-size (10MB) document must complete within 10 seconds; upload progress m=
ust be indicated</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4cc5bfc6-af8e-4ef5-a382-617cd8cc38fb">
<p local-id=3D"83fb0f06aaff"><strong>Session resume:</strong> Loading a ret=
urning user's saved session state must complete within 3 seconds</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6bf19c3f-4d19-4b29-bcb8-0dbea4c5da6b">
<p local-id=3D"67cdd5c2ebb9"><strong>Webhook delivery:</strong> Webhooks mu=
st be delivered within 60 seconds of the triggering event under normal cond=
itions</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c27386ff-4a87-493a-815a-8ea269cd5551">
<p local-id=3D"800552fb2c8f"><strong>Retrieval API:</strong> Applicant data=
 and document endpoints must respond within 5 seconds for a complete sessio=
n dataset</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"72df5b45d8b2"></p>
<hr local-id=3D"6b2faef3-c04a-4e36-be0c-66b7478c3813">
<h2 local-id=3D"0f75740a563b" id=3D"EmbeddableKYCandRiskReviewUI-Non-MVPReq=
uirements">Non-MVP Requirements</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"dfa947b7edd1" id=3D"EmbeddableKYCandRiskReviewUI-Configurab=
leCollectionFlows">Configurable Collection Flows</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"e5d4666a-c985-4f58-99bf-a6107a3bf007">
<li local-id=3D"229007b6-a691-4bf6-ab4a-b1e31305139a">
<p local-id=3D"63bb5d54a0c1">Ability to configure the specific fields and d=
ocuments required to complete each flow</p>
<ul local-id=3D"dfbbe10d-4181-49b5-afa2-694bb88de3c0">
<li local-id=3D"8c41c4a2-32b5-4749-a0aa-9d5a72d0e498">
<p local-id=3D"db3a9c08dabc">Ability to assign specific flows to different =
application clients with a nested configurability layer based on a context =
ID =E2=80=94 one application can support multiple collection flow types</p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"a7eb2959-7b49-4175-abbf-5be67684fcc2">
<p local-id=3D"23c7e2b4142a">Configurable step ordering, not just field sel=
ection</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3c36167c-bb9d-448f-93d1-f28d45889eb5">
<p local-id=3D"8c0c913466c5">Specific forms and fields will be informed by =
future clientele</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"9385956b2456" id=3D"EmbeddableKYCandRiskReviewUI-Localizati=
on">Localization</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"0fb4983b-7b29-4220-a7ed-5588558d2124">
<li local-id=3D"a0c9691d-a806-42ed-b430-28f50662b8d5">
<p local-id=3D"049315262f9a">Full UI string translation for non-English loc=
ales (distinct from country-aware field labeling, which is MVP)</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"d6a372564dba" id=3D"EmbeddableKYCandRiskReviewUI-Operationa=
lTooling">Operational Tooling</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"73414591-1684-4a33-8301-98e8b2cc1a40">
<li local-id=3D"8b007d26-d8d9-47db-b3a6-de6d119d3453">
<p local-id=3D"7cf26f896acf">Admin/ops capability to view session state, tr=
igger re-collection requests, and unlock stalled flows</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"9d0220549d7e" id=3D"EmbeddableKYCandRiskReviewUI-Versioning=
Policy">Versioning Policy</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"deabc226-58d4-46f1-a2c5-e187d805d464">
<li local-id=3D"19325884-9a62-4614-a143-c0637f97ace3">
<p local-id=3D"e1f2bb7e8d5d">Define behavior for in-progress sessions when =
compliance rules change field requirements =E2=80=94 whether sessions are m=
igrated, grandfathered, or invalidated</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"d0bd1197-120a-46fa-a489-2146e306fd40">
<h2 local-id=3D"6d86383d31e5" id=3D"EmbeddableKYCandRiskReviewUI-UserFlow:D=
efaultinformationanddocumentcollectionflowforIndividuals">User Flow: Defaul=
t information and document collection flow for Individuals</h2>
<p local-id=3D"9940f3cc4c45"><em>(not yet made)</em></p>
<h2 local-id=3D"d7764aa7475a" id=3D"EmbeddableKYCandRiskReviewUI-UserFlow:D=
efaultinformationanddocumentcollectionflowforEntities">User Flow: Default i=
nformation and document collection flow for Entities</h2>
<p local-id=3D"147e8a8b7679"><a href=3D"https://ialta-team.atlassian.net/wi=
ki/spaces/IP/pages/934838273/v1+Entity+Verification+Flow+-+Embedded+UI" dat=
a-linked-resource-id=3D"934838273" data-linked-resource-version=3D"3" data-=
linked-resource-type=3D"page">v1 Entity Verification Flow - Embedded UI</a>=
</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"e4ee54cedd7a" id=3D"EmbeddableKYCandRiskReviewUI-OpenQuesti=
ons=E2=80=94Verivend">Open Questions =E2=80=94 Verivend</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"d5=
b531e6-6e20-41bf-9fb9-9ea4d652a0cb" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"3eee8691-0817-4607-bb3d-c0ad927698ce">
<th data-local-id=3D"aae67dd6-ce1a-4d1a-bca7-6999d0660ff1" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"64edabd4a867">Area</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"96e05f92-0be5-48f8-8d17-be504ec30235" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"93dae608ccf4">Question &amp; Context</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"140a3779-f909-4a64-9a6c-d0e25b2ea997" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"e9d0bd413e48">Outcome / Answer</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"2afb7652-0e8a-4f60-b35e-009512b6cdee">
<td data-local-id=3D"29ec2670-fbe0-470f-8ccb-f6b11b980c44" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"63a07a9f14bb">User Flow</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"47b185c4-51f2-48bb-90f8-c20e52ac9e25" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"151a949bbf2a"><strong>Should the primary user be able to ent=
er verification information on behalf of an additional person, and are addi=
tional persons subject to the full IDV workflow independently?</strong> The=
 component is designed around a two-phase model: the primary user enters bi=
ographical data for additional persons (co-holders, beneficial owners), and=
 each additional person then self-verifies via a token-authenticated link s=
ent to them directly. However, there may be scenarios =E2=80=94 such as a s=
pouse physically present during the session =E2=80=94 where requiring a sep=
arate link adds unnecessary friction. If additional persons must independen=
tly complete identity verification (document upload, and potentially livene=
ss/selfie), self-verification is effectively mandatory and the two-phase mo=
del is the only viable path. If document upload is sufficient without liven=
ess, there may be flexibility for the primary user to complete verification=
 on behalf of others in certain cases. The answer to this shapes both the U=
X model for multi-person flows and the IDV requirements we build to.</p></t=
d>
<td data-local-id=3D"ff6a1ef6-a9d8-45ea-a50e-5a086098bd8b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"50369b39f65a"></p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"de9e7633-7708-40d7-805b-2c126b81a344">
<td data-local-id=3D"cee4c886-b541-47c5-b04e-615f66f327d1" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"59ddbf74d022">Correction Flow</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"96d82239-4241-431a-9499-fcacef0dea49" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"db294fea9a92"><strong>See correction flow design question be=
low</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"09a4857b-ca84-4c51-8db4-a8a82ba9f194" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"94b12599afe8"></p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"89c95a74-e0e3-44a4-8bd8-1c3e42d1d873">
<td data-local-id=3D"a26c7095-debe-49b6-8ac8-843f7543f286" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4fb9050d8a3b">Session Lifetime</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"2bbb6b9f-324a-4d18-903c-68b4ba39f29f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ff0956df9c39"><strong>What is the maximum window within whic=
h a partial session should remain resumable =E2=80=94 30 days, 90 days, lon=
ger?</strong> Your requirements doc specifies "weeks" but a hard number is =
needed. A user who starts verification today and returns six weeks later sh=
ould pick up exactly where they left off with all prior data intact. The an=
swer has direct implications for our data retention infrastructure and any =
associated storage costs.</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"52c09cb6-98f5-43d6-b0ad-4ee06979afec" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0730ae37916a"></p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"28e64ce3-9772-410f-8115-e3d785995b94">
<td data-local-id=3D"ae2681c2-e6dc-40a9-abc5-f6d7464c0c03" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"21c6125581a8">Progress Visibility</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"56a0f5b8-9da5-4181-819c-77d38674bd35" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"97bb87095148"><strong>At what point should verification prog=
ress be visible in your native UI =E2=80=94 from the moment the component i=
s first loaded, or only after the first step is completed and saved?</stron=
g> The session status endpoint allows Verivend to display progress (e.g., "=
Verification in progress =E2=80=94 60% complete") on the Verification tab w=
ithout loading the component. Knowing whether you want to reflect a session=
 as "started" the moment it is initialized, or only once substantive data h=
as been saved, determines when we begin emitting progress state.</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"9d3901dc-9e0a-48e2-914b-f67dfe384aed" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e20ab3f75ecd"></p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"4effcbfd-9c47-4ad3-b9b7-2d6ff3116e67">
<td data-local-id=3D"5df1503e-e1b2-445e-a9c3-b8b2fb76a39c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a563eccc03b7">Pre-fill Data</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"5b5c1291-b453-4808-b8ec-56af0bc31f55" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fde38358b825"><strong>What org and user data do you already =
hold that you would want pre-populated into the component at session creati=
on?</strong> For example: legal entity name, registered address, EIN/Tax ID=
, authorized representative name, or contact details already on file in Ver=
ivend. Pre-filling known data reduces friction for the end user and avoids =
asking them to re-enter information Verivend already has. Anything you can =
pass at session initialization we can map to the appropriate fields. A comp=
lete list now allows us to finalize the initialization contract before buil=
d begins.</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"0d9f5cd3-79a4-48e3-a2b8-18c6d24715f8" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4a416b400549"></p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"0bbe5862-5b93-42bb-9e36-983526b05247">
<td data-local-id=3D"21957f2a-22ee-471e-a929-f448817e3963" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fe92cb7af681">Webhook Infrastructure</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"69f3291a-5ed0-4ab0-b836-1ad5fdd906ce" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"17067600df6e"><strong>Do you have existing webhook ingestion=
 infrastructure on your end, or will receiving and processing Interro webho=
oks be net-new build for your team?</strong> Interro will deliver server-si=
de webhooks for step completion, session submission, and screening results.=
 Understanding whether your backend is already set up to receive, verify HM=
AC signatures, and process webhooks =E2=80=94 or whether that is part of yo=
ur integration build =E2=80=94 helps us scope the right level of documentat=
ion and sandbox support to provide.</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"dbadd4e6-f6a1-40cc-8216-abbdbb5deda1" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d89a3330c0b0"></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"e9e72d5b8260" id=3D"EmbeddableKYCandRiskReviewUI-OpenQuesti=
on=E2=80=94CorrectionFlowDesign">Open Question =E2=80=94 Correction Flow De=
sign</h3>
<p local-id=3D"4ba1a73d1aad"><strong>Context:</strong> The component enforc=
es a document quality gate at upload time for entity formation documents, p=
reventing unreadable submissions from reaching reviewers. The remaining cor=
rection scenarios are therefore:</p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"34219bdd-9c17-4be8-8973-efb5a04be0d1">
<li local-id=3D"92d4bae3-5131-444e-bc69-919295d97b79">
<p local-id=3D"a6edec598502"><strong>Entity formation document is valid but=
 wrong</strong> =E2=80=94 e.g. the user uploaded a certificate of good stan=
ding instead of their articles of incorporation. Passes the quality gate; c=
aught by a human reviewer post-submission.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3e4bdb0e-e8f8-4d09-9cda-8dcea8d60c60">
<p local-id=3D"d83b4a3e2b7d"><strong>CIP or AML check failure due to a data=
 entry mismatch</strong> =E2=80=94 e.g. a name typo, incorrect EIN, address=
 inconsistency. A specific field needs to be corrected and the check re-run=
. No document issue involved.</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"ebd7168c149d"><strong>Design question for the group:</strong=
> When a reviewer =E2=80=94 whether a Verivend admin or eventually a GP =E2=
=80=94 returns a submission for corrections, how should that be surfaced to=
 the end user?</p>
<p local-id=3D"6cd0b123ddfe"><strong>Option A =E2=80=94 Reviewer-annotated =
form re-entry:</strong> The reviewer adds notes against specific fields or =
documents before returning the session. The component re-opens the submitte=
d form with those notes visible to the user inline, allowing targeted corre=
ction and resubmission. Higher build complexity; best user experience.</p>
<p local-id=3D"bae14fe6e2ba"><strong>Option B =E2=80=94 Full session reset:=
</strong> A returned session is reset for the specific combination of conte=
xt ID, application, and organization ID. The user re-enters a clean flow wi=
th no inline guidance. Simpler to build; loses targeted correction UX.</p>
<p local-id=3D"b03eda587f22"><strong>The group needs to decide:</strong></p=
>
<ul local-id=3D"67d09723-f676-491c-8b15-d521c3f4aae0">
<li local-id=3D"756dde59-86ee-42f8-b09a-324f818e0dce">
<p local-id=3D"3c869c70397d">Is Option A's annotated re-entry the right MVP=
